cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for object classification. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of linguistic labels to improve the hierarchical representation of objects in the network, which falls under the sub-categories of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.NE are also likely sub-categories.
